    "(17) integrated TCM textbooks and other corpora into the Ziya-LLaMA-13B-V1 model, performing pre-training and instruction fine-tuning on ancient TCM texts to create HuangDi, which provided the model with the ability to answer questions on ancient TCM knowledge.",
    "These studies illustrate the significant potential of LLMs in TCM case record research.",
    "However, several challenges and concerns still emerge in practical applications.",
    "First, the challenge of hallucination (18), wherein the model generates inaccurate or unreliable outputs.",
    "Second, the absence of natural language dialogue-based querying for TCM knowledge graphs."
